From 45cb77991c381b09f78d1cb807b0c29ad64b3deb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 13:04:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add live RSS intelligence feed and i18n support with UI
 localization

### Motivation
- Provide a live intelligence data source to surface near-real-time news, trends and AI insights into the dashboard via RSS and lightweight translation.
- Add localization infrastructure so the UI can switch between English and Chinese and translate UI labels and charts.
- Surface live sync status and translated original links in the UI to improve operational visibility for global F&B teams.

### Description
- Added `src/data/liveData.js` which fetches multiple RSS feeds via `rss2json`, detects categories/countries, translates titles via `translateText`, and synthesizes `news`, `categoryCounts`, `trendSeries`, `socialSeries`, `aiInsights`, `sourceStatus`, and `lastUpdated` returned by `fetchLiveIntelligenceData`.
- Introduced i18n with `src/i18n.jsx` providing `I18nProvider` and `useI18n`, and wrapped the app with `I18nProvider` in `src/main.jsx`.
- Updated `src/App.jsx` to use `useI18n`, to fetch and merge live data into the UI with a periodic hourly refresh (`useEffect` + `setInterval`), to add a language toggle button, and to render a live sync status banner when `liveData` is available.
- Localized many UI strings by switching nav labels and component text to `t(...)`, updated `DonutChart`, `NewsRow`, `Metric`, and `Sidebar` to use translations, and added translated titles and original-link handling to `NewsRow`.

### Testing
- No automated tests were added or executed as part of this change.
